      "content": "The claims are fundamentally rooted in historical assertions by various nations, which they present as inherent sovereign rights. However, international law, particularly the United Nations Convention on the Law of the Sea (UNCLOS), provides a clear framework that many of these expansive claims violate. The international community largely views the expansive claims, especially those based on historical rights that overlap with internationally recognized maritime zones, as legally dubious under modern maritime law.",
