      "content": "UNCLOS provides the definitive legal framework for maritime boundaries, and the international community's skepticism stems from the fact that many of the competing claims directly contradict its established rules. If a claim violates UNCLOS, it is legally invalid under international maritime law, regardless of how long a nation has historically occupied the area. Therefore, the framework itself dictates that the expansive, overlapping claims are not legitimate under current international legal standards.",
